events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Trae Young believes a defensive revival has the Atlanta Hawks back on track. That defense finally showed up in the final quarter against the Los Angeles Lakers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 36 points help streaking Hawks drop Lakers, 129-121

headlines.description: — Reggie Jackson and Brandon Boston Jr. each scored 19 points, and the Los Angeles Clippers routed the Charlotte Hornets 115-90 on Sunday to improve to 4-3 on their current road trip.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson, Boston lead Clippers' rout of Hornets, 115-90

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 24 points and 14 rebounds, DeMar DeRozan added 23 points and 10 assists and the Chicago Bulls overcame a slow to start to beat the Portland Trail Blazers 130-116 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic, DeRozan help Bulls beat Trail Blazers 130-116

headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey scored 31 points, Cade Cunningham had 19 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists and the Detroit Pistons overcame a terrible start to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 115-105 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bey, Cunningham key Pistons' rally in 115-105 win over Cavs

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 18 points, including the tiebreaking layup with 54 seconds remaining, and the Orlando Magic overcame Luka Doncic’s seventh triple-double of the season to beat the Dallas Mavericks 110-108 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner gets go-ahead layup in Magic's 110-108 win over Mavs

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 18 points, 15 assists and nine rebounds to help the Denver Nuggets rout the Milwaukee Bucks 136-100 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic, Nuggets rout defending champ Bucks 136-100

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 31 points, 11 rebounds and 10 assists, Jaden McDaniels scored a season-high 22 points off the bench, and the Timberwolves routed the shorthanded Utah Jazz 126-106 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns scores 31 in Wolves' win over Jazz; Ingles injured

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Chris Paul has been to the All-Star Game 11 times in his NBA career and — barring a mammoth snub — is headed there for No. 12 next month.
headlines.shortLinkText: NBA-best Suns rally for 10th straight win, top Spurs 115-110
